HEADWORD: Tardigrade
<hw>Tar"di*grade</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tardigradus</ets>; <ets>tardus</ets> slow + <ets>gradi</ets> to
step: cf. F. <ets>tardigrade</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Moving or
stepping slowly; slow-paced.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>G.
Eliot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the
